1
00:00:08,667 --> 00:00:11,100
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:11,100 --> 00:00:12,467
Alright, thank you.

3
00:00:12,667 --> 00:00:15,500
Everyone thinks this job is
clipboards and signatures.

4
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:18,000
Actually, it's surveillance.

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,733
And luckily, my co-supervisor
sees everything.

6
00:00:20,733 --> 00:00:23,600
The living, the dead,
and the slacking.

7
00:00:24,367 --> 00:00:25,700
Thank you.

8
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:31,233
[ROS SNORES]

9
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:35,433
[SNORES]

10
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:41,767
[CACKLES]

11
00:00:42,733 --> 00:00:44,067
[CLEARS THROAT]

12
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:45,767
[GROANS] Hmph!

13
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:47,633
[MOANS] Hmm.

14
00:00:50,033 --> 00:00:51,433
Tess! Stop it!

15
00:00:51,733 --> 00:00:54,267
I'm sleeping!
Stop messing with me!

16
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:59,033
[TESS] Hey, Ms. Ros! Your break
ended ten minutes ago!

17
00:00:59,033 --> 00:01:00,633
You know,
if you weren't dead,

18
00:01:00,633 --> 00:01:03,367
I'll shove my foot down
your throat.

19
00:01:03,367 --> 00:01:06,467
Hi, Ros! Break ended at 9:05.

20
00:01:07,367 --> 00:01:08,333
[SIGHS]

21
00:01:08,700 --> 00:01:10,233
Noa,

22
00:01:10,433 --> 00:01:13,800
can you please tell your mom
to stop doing that to me,

23
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:18,200
or I'm going to spill all
her dirty little secrets!

24
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:19,633
You're always late.

25
00:01:19,633 --> 00:01:21,400
And your feet
are full of callous.

26
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:24,133
I thought my tickling powers
would go to waste.

27
00:01:24,433 --> 00:01:25,333
[ROS] Hey, Tess!

28
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:26,467
You heard me, right?

29
00:01:27,367 --> 00:01:28,467
Mom said, she'll stop.

30
00:01:29,300 --> 00:01:30,267
Okay.

31
00:01:30,267 --> 00:01:31,233
Good.

32
00:01:32,733 --> 00:01:33,733
[GASPS]

33
00:01:33,733 --> 00:01:40,667
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

34
00:01:44,633 --> 00:01:46,367
Want a snack?

35
00:01:46,367 --> 00:01:47,467
Yes, please.

36
00:01:50,433 --> 00:01:52,767
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

37
00:01:57,867 --> 00:02:00,533
[CURIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

38
00:02:00,533 --> 00:02:02,133
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

39
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:12,200
[CURIOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

40
00:02:14,167 --> 00:02:15,400
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

41
00:02:17,233 --> 00:02:18,567
[GROANS IN PAIN]

42
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:21,767
I'm sorry, we didn't know
we had another

43
00:02:21,767 --> 00:02:23,567
overflow patient
being brought in.

44
00:02:28,133 --> 00:02:29,133
Jane Doe?

45
00:02:29,133 --> 00:02:31,333
Listen, lady. I just
rolled the beds, okay?

46
00:02:31,333 --> 00:02:33,700
All I know is that she
collapsed in the grocery store.

47
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:38,267
Hi, I'm Noa.

48
00:02:38,633 --> 00:02:40,133
How can we help you?

49
00:02:41,133 --> 00:02:43,167
Dear, it hurts.

50
00:02:43,433 --> 00:02:45,800
I can't take it anymore.
My stomach hurts.

51
00:02:46,267 --> 00:02:48,167
Don't worry,
we'll take care of you.

52
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:49,333
Do you have an ID?

53
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:51,467
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

54
00:02:58,433 --> 00:03:00,667
Sorry,
I don't have one right now.

55
00:03:00,667 --> 00:03:03,233
Uh-oh, TNT vibes.

56
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:04,600
That's okay.

57
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:05,667
Do you have an address?

58
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:07,333
Uh...

59
00:03:07,933 --> 00:03:10,933
12 Greenhills Subdivision.

60
00:03:10,933 --> 00:03:13,300
Yep, that confirms it.

61
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:14,800
[CLEARS THROAT]

62
00:03:17,533 --> 00:03:18,633
Ma'am?

63
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:25,267
There's no subdivisions
here in America.

64
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:26,667
Is she stupid?

65
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:29,400
My intestine is in pain!

66
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,733
I'm not deaf!

67
00:03:30,733 --> 00:03:31,933
It's fine.

68
00:03:32,767 --> 00:03:34,433
Let's move her to...

69
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:37,633
Room 511.

70
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:41,367
Huh? Why are you
putting her in my room?

71
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:44,433
Noa? A word.

72
00:03:47,533 --> 00:03:49,367
[ROS] I need to tell you
something important.

73
00:03:49,367 --> 00:03:50,500
Come here!

74
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:54,667
Noa, don't trigger
the silver alert yet.

75
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:55,600
That's protocol.

76
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,433
How's her family supposed
to find her?

77
00:03:59,767 --> 00:04:01,967
Do you know what they
do to people with no papers?

78
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:04,400
Especially with an accent
as thick as that?

79
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:05,700
I'm not breaking the rules.

80
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:06,933
[GROANS] Ugh!

81
00:04:06,933 --> 00:04:08,467
Excuse me, ladies.

82
00:04:08,467 --> 00:04:10,433
Can I ask you a question?

83
00:04:10,433 --> 00:04:14,333
No, we're not talking to
ghosts here, you crazy person.

84
00:04:14,333 --> 00:04:15,467
Go back to work!

85
00:04:15,467 --> 00:04:17,333
Okay, Ros, don't gaslight me.

86
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:18,700
I know what gaslighting is.

87
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:20,567
That's the same tool I
use making you all believe

88
00:04:20,567 --> 00:04:22,967
I can only speak Spanish
and my real name is Atzin.

89
00:04:22,967 --> 00:04:25,333
Wait, your real name
is not Atzin?

90
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:27,333
I definitely don't like secrets.

91
00:04:27,367 --> 00:04:29,033
They don't care if your
name is James Ingram.

92
00:04:29,033 --> 00:04:31,000
Just mind your own business. Go!

93
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,567
[SPEAKING IN FRENCH] Don’t tell
me to mind my own business!

94
00:04:32,567 --> 00:04:33,533
When you tell me
not to do something,

95
00:04:33,533 --> 00:04:34,800
I’m gonna do it anyway!

96
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,333
I’ll show you what
a real<i> chismosa</i> is...

97
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:37,633
Whatever!

98
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:40,900
Where am I again?

99
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:42,733
Minding your own business?

100
00:04:43,767 --> 00:04:44,600
Ah.

101
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:47,367
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING,
FADES]

102
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,967
Can you at least tell me
anyone's phone number?

103
00:04:53,967 --> 00:04:55,700
[TESS] Oh, is that so?

104
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:59,900
You brought her here so that
I can be your Tagalog tutor?

105
00:05:02,033 --> 00:05:03,533
What is your...

106
00:05:03,867 --> 00:05:05,000
No, no...

107
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,900
What is your...

108
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,000
phone number?

109
00:05:10,433 --> 00:05:12,600
I failed as a mother.

110
00:05:14,633 --> 00:05:15,567
Alright.

111
00:05:15,567 --> 00:05:17,033
- Maybe we can start with...
- [GROANS]

112
00:05:17,033 --> 00:05:18,267
- [PHONE THUDS]- Oh!

113
00:05:19,733 --> 00:05:20,967
[GROANS IN PAIN]

114
00:05:20,967 --> 00:05:22,600
What is it? Where's the pain?

115
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,700
Flip phone?

116
00:05:24,333 --> 00:05:27,300
[CHUCKLES] It's like 1997.

117
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,033
You're not helping.

118
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:34,000
Whatever happens,
don't call them.

119
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,600
[GROANING IN PAIN]

120
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:43,633
Excuse me.

121
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:46,367
[JANE] Sir.

122
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:48,300
Bruh.

123
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:50,900
- You're ward five, right?
- Yup.

124
00:05:54,033 --> 00:05:55,933
It says you're off today.

125
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:59,667
Is Noa making you come in
on your mandated rest day?

126
00:06:00,367 --> 00:06:01,700
Well, yes.

127
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:02,967
Actually, she's a...

128
00:06:04,067 --> 00:06:05,767
She's a slave driver.

129
00:06:05,767 --> 00:06:06,767
[JANE] What?

130
00:06:06,767 --> 00:06:07,733
Yeah.

131
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:09,567
Not on my watch.

132
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:12,533
You go be with family.

133
00:06:12,533 --> 00:06:13,700
Touch grass.

134
00:06:13,700 --> 00:06:16,567
I don't care. Just not here.

135
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:18,667
Family...

136
00:06:19,433 --> 00:06:23,400
If I see you in here,
I'm writing you up.

137
00:06:24,100 --> 00:06:25,067
It's payday.

138
00:06:26,033 --> 00:06:27,033
Live a little.

139
00:06:28,467 --> 00:06:29,867
Right... right.

140
00:06:29,867 --> 00:06:31,967
[INHALES SHARPLY, SIGHS]

141
00:06:31,967 --> 00:06:34,467
- Uh...
- Go live a little.

142
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:37,367
[SIGHS] Yeah, of course.

143
00:06:37,367 --> 00:06:44,100
[BRIGHT UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

144
00:06:59,167 --> 00:07:06,133
[BRIGHT UPBEAT MUSIC CONTINUES]

145
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,100
[SNIFFS]

146
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:20,433
[MUSIC FADES]

147
00:07:23,533 --> 00:07:26,733
[TESS] It's a miracle.
Dr. Morris answered their phone.

148
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,567
We needed the order.

149
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,600
Plus, she's a little altered,

150
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,933
so UA should let us know
if this is infection-related.

151
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:34,700
[ROS] Hey!

152
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:38,000
What's urine got to do
with confusion?

153
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,800
UTIs are the most
common reason

154
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,967
why older folks become
suddenly confused.

155
00:07:42,967 --> 00:07:44,267
Ah,

156
00:07:44,267 --> 00:07:48,733
so that's why Tess is always
nagging me to get a urine test.

157
00:07:50,067 --> 00:07:51,433
Hey, Tess!

158
00:07:51,633 --> 00:07:54,000
If I become a ghost,
you better watch out!

159
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,833
I'll tear your hair off
one by one!

160
00:07:56,633 --> 00:07:57,833
[PHONE RINGING]

161
00:07:59,567 --> 00:08:00,867
[PHONE RINGING]

162
00:08:02,767 --> 00:08:04,133
Answer it.

163
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:08,433
[SIGHS] She practically begged
me not to contact anyone.

164
00:08:08,667 --> 00:08:10,600
- [PHONE RINGING]
- Then respect her wishes.

165
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:12,133
Why would you listen to Ros?

166
00:08:12,133 --> 00:08:14,700
Maybe her family
is worried for her!

167
00:08:15,133 --> 00:08:17,900
Maybe that person
knows her family.

168
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:19,000
[PHONE RINGING]

169
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:22,533
[ROS SCOFFS] That's not
a contact.

170
00:08:23,167 --> 00:08:24,567
That's a warning.

171
00:08:25,167 --> 00:08:32,167
[CURIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

172
00:08:33,167 --> 00:08:35,033
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

173
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:39,867
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

174
00:08:39,867 --> 00:08:40,933
Welcome!

175
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:44,133
OMG, Dolce.

176
00:08:44,533 --> 00:08:46,500
I used to have one,
but it ran away.

177
00:08:46,733 --> 00:08:48,267
Either that,
or I left it at CVS.

178
00:08:48,267 --> 00:08:50,233
- Either way, respect.
- Where is she?

179
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:51,833
Hi, Beatrice?

180
00:08:52,033 --> 00:08:53,167
- Yes.
- She's resting right now.

181
00:08:53,567 --> 00:08:54,867
Thank God, we were so worried.

182
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:57,900
(In Tagalog) See? I told you,
it's a good idea to call them.

183
00:08:58,100 --> 00:09:01,600
The boss can also
call the family members.

184
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:03,233
Is she your mom?

185
00:09:03,633 --> 00:09:04,833
- Yes.
- No. She's not.

186
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:07,067
But she's like family.

187
00:09:07,767 --> 00:09:09,267
Is she okay?
What happened to her?

188
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:12,033
She's okay. We gave her
medication for the pain,

189
00:09:12,033 --> 00:09:14,667
but we're gonna need
full consent for a CT scan.

190
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,033
A CT?

191
00:09:16,267 --> 00:09:18,000
Yeah, it could be
something serious.

192
00:09:18,900 --> 00:09:20,800
We can't afford that.

193
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:26,633
Girl, I know the perfect
pawn shop for your bag

194
00:09:26,633 --> 00:09:28,033
if you need some extra cash.

195
00:09:29,233 --> 00:09:30,600
Oh, foot in mouth?

196
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,233
I'll go take my break now.

197
00:09:34,133 --> 00:09:35,533
Yeah.

198
00:09:38,567 --> 00:09:45,300
- [PRAYING IN SPANISH]
- [QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

199
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:48,633
[DOOR OPENS]

200
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:51,867
Oh...

201
00:09:51,867 --> 00:09:53,667
- [EGG CRACKS]
- my god.

202
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:56,767
I didn't see anything.

203
00:09:57,333 --> 00:09:58,633
I am just...

204
00:09:59,133 --> 00:10:00,633
uh, looking for my lunchables.

205
00:10:01,067 --> 00:10:02,933
Uh... [STAMMERS]

206
00:10:02,933 --> 00:10:05,000
it's fine. You can look.

207
00:10:06,033 --> 00:10:07,067
[SIGHS]

208
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:09,067
If I look, legally,

209
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:11,100
I have to report it.
I don't know to whom.

210
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:13,267
But still,
that did not look right.

211
00:10:13,967 --> 00:10:16,267
I'm doing
what my grandma used to do.

212
00:10:16,267 --> 00:10:17,567
She was a faith healer.

213
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:19,100
And I'm a Christian,

214
00:10:19,100 --> 00:10:20,867
so I'm used to
the whole golden rule thing.

215
00:10:21,333 --> 00:10:22,300
What?

216
00:10:22,700 --> 00:10:23,733
Don't judge others

217
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:25,867
and get judgmental karmic acne,
or whatever.

218
00:10:26,633 --> 00:10:27,767
Right.

219
00:10:28,167 --> 00:10:29,700
What are you
doing that for, anyway?

220
00:10:30,233 --> 00:10:31,967
Haven't you ever wanted
to communicate

221
00:10:31,967 --> 00:10:33,267
with the ghosts in this ward?

222
00:10:33,267 --> 00:10:35,067
[SCOFFS] Did Camille tell you?

223
00:10:35,333 --> 00:10:36,900
I ghosted that guy from Tinder.

224
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:39,100
He looked nothing
like his profile picture.

225
00:10:39,833 --> 00:10:41,000
Never mind.

226
00:10:42,333 --> 00:10:44,367
Wait, like ghost ghosts?

227
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:47,167
Because I know how to
open someone's third eye.

228
00:10:47,167 --> 00:10:51,633
[QURIKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

229
00:10:52,167 --> 00:10:54,133
[WHISPERS]
What? Is that true? Really?

230
00:10:54,133 --> 00:10:57,967
- [MONITOR BEEPING]
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

231
00:10:57,967 --> 00:10:59,600
- Go watch the kids.
- Okay.

232
00:11:02,067 --> 00:11:04,000
We were so worried about you.

233
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,733
- I doubt that.
- Ros!

234
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,200
No, Noa.

235
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,800
You were not
supposed to call them.

236
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:10,200
That's what she asked for!

237
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,733
We follow protocol.

238
00:11:12,067 --> 00:11:14,800
Do you even know what
these people have done to her?

239
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:16,233
Who the hell
do you think you are?

240
00:11:16,233 --> 00:11:18,200
If she did not collapse
in the grocery,

241
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:21,033
nobody would ever know what
you have been doing to her!

242
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:24,300
(In Tagalog) I just wanted to
take a little break,

243
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:26,333
before I go back to...

244
00:11:26,333 --> 00:11:28,167
She's just making up
an excuse.

245
00:11:28,167 --> 00:11:30,200
- That's not true.
- Tell them.

246
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:32,967
Tell them how much you're
getting paid to be their maid.

247
00:11:32,967 --> 00:11:35,167
- But she's like family.
- Liar!

248
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:37,133
This is labor, and she's abused.

249
00:11:37,133 --> 00:11:38,733
- Ros, go outside.
- Don't even bother.

250
00:11:38,733 --> 00:11:39,767
- Now!
- No!

251
00:11:40,167 --> 00:11:42,067
- What is...
- I'm so sorry, folks.

252
00:11:42,833 --> 00:11:43,800
Ros!

253
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,667
- [ROS GRUNTS]
- [NOA SIGHS]

254
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,200
[NOA] Ros!

255
00:11:50,067 --> 00:11:57,033
- [BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

256
00:12:12,967 --> 00:12:14,067
[BRIGHT MUSIC FADES]

257
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:16,733
[NOA] Ros!

258
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:18,867
Ros!

259
00:12:19,067 --> 00:12:20,167
Please give us a minute.

260
00:12:21,867 --> 00:12:23,133
Ros!

261
00:12:23,333 --> 00:12:25,933
You don't hurl accusations
at patients like that.

262
00:12:26,767 --> 00:12:29,333
Just because she's old
doesn't mean she's confused.

263
00:12:29,733 --> 00:12:31,067
It's not our place.

264
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,267
This is all your fault.

265
00:12:34,267 --> 00:12:35,933
You shouldn't have called them.

266
00:12:36,967 --> 00:12:38,233
Trust me, Ros.

267
00:12:38,433 --> 00:12:40,467
I can't break any more rules
than I already have.

268
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:41,867
How about you trust me, huh?

269
00:12:42,067 --> 00:12:44,167
Your mom may be
a pain in my ass,

270
00:12:44,167 --> 00:12:46,400
but she well knew
enough to listen.

271
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:50,333
I may not have your degrees,
or your straight A's.

272
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:53,367
But I have been there.

273
00:12:55,267 --> 00:12:57,233
I have been there!

274
00:12:57,233 --> 00:12:58,433
- Ros!
- [TESS] Noa!

275
00:12:58,433 --> 00:12:59,433
Shhh!

276
00:13:00,033 --> 00:13:01,067
Let's listen.

277
00:13:03,167 --> 00:13:04,367
[NOA SIGHS]

278
00:13:07,467 --> 00:13:08,433
I'm listening.

279
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:15,133
[ROS TAPPING]

280
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:24,033
When I came to America,

281
00:13:25,533 --> 00:13:27,100
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

282
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:30,267
I was desperate to send money
to the Philippines.

283
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:37,333
Desperate for my son.

284
00:13:40,267 --> 00:13:41,367
He's special.

285
00:13:44,467 --> 00:13:46,400
I was a caregiver
in the facility.

286
00:13:48,067 --> 00:13:51,333
This Filipino sponsor
seems so nice.

287
00:13:52,367 --> 00:13:55,300
And you know,
I have this sense of gratitude.

288
00:13:58,433 --> 00:14:00,433
But then it became nonstop.

289
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,267
Every day.

290
00:14:07,233 --> 00:14:08,467
Every hour.

291
00:14:09,867 --> 00:14:11,800
Seven years.

292
00:14:12,367 --> 00:14:14,000
With no day off.

293
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:17,000
Why didn't you just leave?

294
00:14:17,267 --> 00:14:18,233
How could I?

295
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:20,900
She kept my passport.

296
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:22,900
I'm so sorry.

297
00:14:23,533 --> 00:14:25,167
Not until I saw the flyers

298
00:14:25,167 --> 00:14:27,500
of the Filipino Workers Center
here in LA.

299
00:14:28,533 --> 00:14:30,000
Led me to the consulate.

300
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:32,600
Then the FBI got involved.

301
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:39,067
I couldn't even make a call.

302
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:45,467
She said long distance
was too expensive.

303
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:51,500
I can't talk to my son.

304
00:14:53,633 --> 00:14:56,100
I can't even listen
to his voice.

305
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,433
It hurts.

306
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:05,567
You don't know how lucky you are
that you've been born here.

307
00:15:07,333 --> 00:15:08,333
We...

308
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:11,367
we bleed just to get here.

309
00:15:12,300 --> 00:15:13,400
Ros.

310
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:16,500
I'm so sorry
you went through that.

311
00:15:17,367 --> 00:15:18,333
[ROS SNIFFLES]

312
00:15:19,567 --> 00:15:20,600
[ROS EXHALES]

313
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:24,867
Noa.

314
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:27,933
I don't need your pity.

315
00:15:29,033 --> 00:15:30,300
Especially you, Tess.

316
00:15:32,267 --> 00:15:34,233
I don't pity you, Ros.

317
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:37,067
I hate you most of the time.

318
00:15:37,667 --> 00:15:38,600
But...

319
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:41,533
I always respect you.

320
00:15:45,967 --> 00:15:47,167
Is she saying something?

321
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:51,033
She loves you
more than she'd like to admit.

322
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:52,267
Oh.

323
00:15:53,933 --> 00:15:55,967
So, what do you suggest we do?

324
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:58,167
It's not like you have
those consulate contacts

325
00:15:58,167 --> 00:15:59,300
on speed dial.

326
00:16:04,167 --> 00:16:05,167
What if I do?

327
00:16:06,033 --> 00:16:07,367
I wouldn't know what to say.

328
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:08,567
Uh...

329
00:16:10,333 --> 00:16:11,400
you think...

330
00:16:12,367 --> 00:16:15,033
you can hold them long enough?

331
00:16:16,367 --> 00:16:17,533
[WHISPERS] I have a plan.

332
00:16:17,967 --> 00:16:18,933
[TESS] Wow.

333
00:16:19,233 --> 00:16:21,167
Now she has a plan?

334
00:16:24,267 --> 00:16:25,567
I don't know. I don't know.

335
00:16:26,167 --> 00:16:27,500
I get it.

336
00:16:28,967 --> 00:16:31,967
It's so hard to trust.
It's always just been you two.

337
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:35,367
I'm not asking for forever.

338
00:16:36,733 --> 00:16:37,700
Noa.

339
00:16:38,567 --> 00:16:40,033
Just this once.

340
00:16:40,567 --> 00:16:41,533
Hmm?

341
00:16:44,667 --> 00:16:45,633
Okay.

342
00:16:46,533 --> 00:16:47,500
I'll follow.

343
00:16:47,767 --> 00:16:48,733
You lead.

344
00:16:50,567 --> 00:16:51,733
(In Tagalog) Hey, Tess.

345
00:16:52,533 --> 00:16:53,667
You heard that?

346
00:16:54,267 --> 00:16:55,700
I'm being a good girl here.

347
00:16:55,700 --> 00:16:58,633
So don't you dare
use magic on me

348
00:16:58,633 --> 00:17:01,067
with your unspecified
ghostly powers.

349
00:17:05,100 --> 00:17:06,200
Just three hours.

350
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,367
Okay.

351
00:17:07,367 --> 00:17:08,333
[WHISPERS] Okay?

352
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:09,333
Three.

353
00:17:10,133 --> 00:17:11,133
[DOOR OPENS]

354
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:22,733
- [BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]
- [WAVES CRASHING]

355
00:17:37,733 --> 00:17:44,667
[BRIGHT MUSIC CONTINUES]

356
00:17:50,667 --> 00:17:52,033
[MUSIC FADES]

357
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:54,767
When do we get the results?

358
00:17:56,667 --> 00:17:57,733
Oh, you can go.

359
00:17:58,600 --> 00:17:59,667
Oh, here they are.

360
00:17:59,667 --> 00:18:06,600
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

361
00:18:12,667 --> 00:18:14,400
Our Consul General from

362
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:16,700
the Philippine Consulate General
of Los Angeles,

363
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:18,133
ConGen Adel.

364
00:18:19,667 --> 00:18:20,767
[MUSIC FADES]

365
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:22,467
And that lady over there,

366
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:25,500
our PWC representative,
Ms. Malou Villacisneros.

367
00:18:25,767 --> 00:18:28,667
The President of SIPA,
Ms. Kimmy Maniquis.

368
00:18:29,133 --> 00:18:30,433
[SCOFFS] What is this?

369
00:18:30,867 --> 00:18:32,200
This is so cool.

370
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:34,733
It's like a mafia movie,
but like, with good people.

371
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:37,833
We're here to assist Nanny Linda
in coordinate support

372
00:18:37,833 --> 00:18:40,267
from the Philippine government
for a distressed citizen.

373
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:42,500
Wow, you can do that?

374
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:45,300
Yes, of course. We are mandated
by the Philippine government

375
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:47,333
to promote
and protect the welfare

376
00:18:47,333 --> 00:18:49,333
of every Filipina
wherever they are.

377
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:51,467
- Wow!
- Mm-hmm.

378
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:53,633
And the lady over there,
Miss Malou,

379
00:18:53,633 --> 00:18:54,767
our PWC representative,

380
00:18:55,267 --> 00:18:56,867
is here to help find

381
00:18:56,867 --> 00:19:00,433
Nanny Linda's
closest living relative.

382
00:19:00,433 --> 00:19:02,300
You can't do this.
I'm going to sue all of you.

383
00:19:02,300 --> 00:19:04,233
She's not even a citizen.

384
00:19:04,233 --> 00:19:05,667
I'm actually here
to help out with that.

385
00:19:06,733 --> 00:19:08,733
Mario Salgada, MTS Law.

386
00:19:08,733 --> 00:19:10,500
Oh, that's ridiculous.
You cannot do that.

387
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:14,533
You don't get to intimidate
staff and patients here.

388
00:19:15,233 --> 00:19:16,367
Step back.

389
00:19:16,567 --> 00:19:17,533
Now.

390
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:20,400
Actually, as her counsel,

391
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:22,600
I'll be filing criminal
and civil complaints.

392
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:26,433
We are here to advocate
for Nanny Linda.

393
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:28,800
Mm-hmm. And I'm sure

394
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:32,500
Nanny Linda will be
more than happy to sue you

395
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:36,767
for 30 years of unpaid labor

396
00:19:36,767 --> 00:19:40,500
for three generations
of your family,

397
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:41,667
not hers.

398
00:19:41,867 --> 00:19:45,467
Ooh, girl, you are in trouble.

399
00:19:45,933 --> 00:19:47,600
You might want to pawn
that bag now.

400
00:19:47,867 --> 00:19:49,467
I totally know a place.

401
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:53,167
Hi.

402
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:58,167
It's time to roll you over
to Imaging now.

403
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:00,400
(In Tagalog)
But that's expensive, right?

404
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:04,267
There are some nice people here.

405
00:20:04,533 --> 00:20:06,333
They are going
to take care of that for you.

406
00:20:08,767 --> 00:20:09,733
(In Tagalog) Ma'am,

407
00:20:10,433 --> 00:20:11,933
we have a surprise for you.

408
00:20:13,667 --> 00:20:18,900
We've found your
relatives on social media.

409
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:31,500
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

410
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:33,800
[LINDA WHIMPERING]

411
00:20:36,967 --> 00:20:39,400
[LINDA INHALES, SNIFFLES]

412
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:44,933
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

413
00:20:44,933 --> 00:20:48,800
[LINDA CRYING]

414
00:20:51,767 --> 00:20:55,767
[LINDA SNIFFLES, CRYING]

415
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:01,667
[LINDA SNIFFLES, WHIMPERS]

416
00:21:03,733 --> 00:21:06,267
[LINDA SNIFFLES, WHIMPERING]

417
00:21:06,267 --> 00:21:09,500
[WHEELS ROLLING]

418
00:21:11,900 --> 00:21:18,867
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

419
00:21:18,867 --> 00:21:25,833
[WHEELS ROLLING]

420
00:21:27,667 --> 00:21:28,933
[DISINFECTANT SPRAYS]

421
00:21:30,833 --> 00:21:31,800
[DOOR OPENS]

422
00:21:34,533 --> 00:21:35,700
[DOOR CLOSES]

423
00:21:35,700 --> 00:21:36,633
[DISINFECTANT SPRAYS]

424
00:21:36,633 --> 00:21:38,700
I asked everyone
at the nurse's station.

425
00:21:38,700 --> 00:21:40,967
I even texted Camille,
George, Grim...

426
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,000
No luck.

427
00:21:43,033 --> 00:21:44,467
Lapis lazuli.

428
00:21:44,467 --> 00:21:45,967
It's supposed
to open someone's third eye.

429
00:21:46,767 --> 00:21:49,000
- How do you know that?
- ChatGPT.

430
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,367
No one had it,
so I ordered one for you.

431
00:21:51,900 --> 00:21:52,800
[JOSH GASPS]

432
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:55,667
Wow, that's--
that's very nice of you.

433
00:21:55,667 --> 00:21:56,767
If Noa's taught me anything,

434
00:21:56,767 --> 00:22:00,300
this job is about people,
not just the work work.

435
00:22:01,067 --> 00:22:02,400
Hey, um...

436
00:22:03,367 --> 00:22:06,467
W-Would you be down
for dinner sometime?

437
00:22:06,467 --> 00:22:08,467
Maybe ghost hunting?

438
00:22:09,733 --> 00:22:12,033
I'll bring snacks.
And holy water.

439
00:22:12,867 --> 00:22:14,033
Y-You have my number?

440
00:22:14,700 --> 00:22:15,667
Yeah, saved.

441
00:22:16,333 --> 00:22:17,700
I just couldn't spell your name.

442
00:22:17,700 --> 00:22:20,567
Oh. Real name's Josh.

443
00:22:21,867 --> 00:22:23,800
You're, like, totally blowing
my mind.

444
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:26,333
Well, Josh is too approachable.

445
00:22:27,567 --> 00:22:30,067
Well, text me if
anything starts floating, Josh.

446
00:22:30,067 --> 00:22:31,067
[JOSH CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

447
00:22:31,067 --> 00:22:38,067
[PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

448
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:48,933
[WHOOSHING]

449
00:22:48,967 --> 00:22:50,767
Where did you go?

450
00:22:50,767 --> 00:22:53,700
Did you think I wouldn't notice
that you did a side quest?

451
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:57,067
Day off.

452
00:22:58,133 --> 00:23:00,700
Day off?
Then what are you doing here?

453
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:02,633
Don't you know
how to enjoy yourself?

454
00:23:03,833 --> 00:23:10,767
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

455
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:28,100
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

456
00:23:29,933 --> 00:23:31,033
Immortality.

457
00:23:33,933 --> 00:23:35,933
It's lonelier than I realized.

458
00:23:38,467 --> 00:23:39,600
[GRIM INHALES]

459
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:42,100
Now I understand why
you're so close to each other.

460
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:47,100
The hourglass moves too fast.

461
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:51,900
Wow, do you have
a translation for that?

462
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:52,867
[GRIM CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

463
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:58,000
[TESS BREATHES DEEPLY]

464
00:24:02,067 --> 00:24:04,467
[FABRIC RUSTLING]

465
00:24:05,167 --> 00:24:06,167
[GRIM INHALES]

466
00:24:07,833 --> 00:24:08,900
[TESS] I think...

467
00:24:10,167 --> 00:24:12,900
You're not here
to tell me anything.

468
00:24:14,767 --> 00:24:16,400
[GRIM CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

469
00:24:16,867 --> 00:24:20,400
You should be thankful that
I'm here, not because of you.

470
00:24:21,967 --> 00:24:24,733
It's another excuse
for your daughter to hate me.

471
00:24:29,467 --> 00:24:30,467
What a shame.

472
00:24:31,633 --> 00:24:34,600
I really thought
it would end well.

473
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:38,733
That is neither
good nor bad, Tess.

474
00:24:38,733 --> 00:24:40,033
It simply is.

475
00:24:43,133 --> 00:24:44,667
[TESS INHALES]

476
00:24:44,667 --> 00:24:45,600
Maybe...

477
00:24:46,233 --> 00:24:48,133
I should be the one to tell her.

478
00:24:48,133 --> 00:24:50,967
She might be asleep
in front of the computer again.

479
00:24:53,133 --> 00:24:54,500
Don't worry.

480
00:24:55,867 --> 00:24:58,433
I gave her some extra time
to say goodbye.

481
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:02,500
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

482
00:25:02,533 --> 00:25:03,567
[TESS GASPS IN AMAZEMENT]

483
00:25:05,033 --> 00:25:06,000
You know...

484
00:25:06,667 --> 00:25:09,133
You're not
as bad as I thought.

485
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:25,167
[WHOOSHING]

486
00:25:27,100 --> 00:25:28,500
[GROANS]

487
00:25:28,500 --> 00:25:30,467
Mom, I'm still sleeping.

488
00:25:33,067 --> 00:25:34,167
[GROANS SOFTLY]

489
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:40,000
[GROANS]

490
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:45,867
[WHEELS ROLLING]

491
00:25:45,867 --> 00:25:47,033
[NOA GROANS]

492
00:25:49,867 --> 00:25:51,100
Oh.

493
00:25:51,100 --> 00:25:52,900
You're back
from imaging already?

494
00:25:56,000 --> 00:26:01,833
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

495
00:26:01,833 --> 00:26:03,833
No! No, no, no, no!

496
00:26:04,967 --> 00:26:06,500
[CHAIR SWIVELS, THUDS]

497
00:26:08,967 --> 00:26:10,000
[NOA EXHALES]

498
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:13,233
- He did this.
- He said you would say that.

499
00:26:14,233 --> 00:26:15,767
He also told me

500
00:26:15,767 --> 00:26:19,700
how hard you're fighting
to keep your mom here.

501
00:26:21,767 --> 00:26:22,800
[NOA SCOFFS]

502
00:26:24,033 --> 00:26:26,600
He's really trying
to piss me off.

503
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:29,733
I don't think spite
is their purpose, dear.

504
00:26:30,933 --> 00:26:35,233
Because you can't keep her here
for the rest of your life.

505
00:26:35,933 --> 00:26:38,167
She's all I have.

506
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:41,300
There are more people out there.

507
00:26:43,100 --> 00:26:46,133
There are a lot of people
waiting for me.

508
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:48,333
Exactly!

509
00:26:50,233 --> 00:26:53,900
We just helped you!
They were going to fly you back

510
00:26:53,900 --> 00:26:56,067
to the Philippines
to see your family.

511
00:26:56,067 --> 00:26:59,067
I've been sick for a long time.

512
00:26:59,933 --> 00:27:02,300
I think you already know that.

513
00:27:03,900 --> 00:27:04,900
[NOA SIGHS]

514
00:27:06,933 --> 00:27:09,933
[NOA BREATHES DEEPLY]

515
00:27:11,867 --> 00:27:13,633
Don't cry.

516
00:27:16,733 --> 00:27:18,200
You know what?

517
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:25,300
You've given me more than my
whole 30 years here in America.

518
00:27:25,300 --> 00:27:29,067
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

519
00:27:29,067 --> 00:27:30,633
That's not fair.

520
00:27:31,700 --> 00:27:33,867
When did life become fair?

521
00:27:34,900 --> 00:27:38,133
When were we given
this kind of miracle?

522
00:27:39,233 --> 00:27:44,233
That's what you gave me.
You and Ros.

523
00:27:44,233 --> 00:27:49,367
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

524
00:27:49,400 --> 00:27:50,867
You can't stay?

525
00:27:52,667 --> 00:27:54,267
What for, dear?

526
00:27:56,767 --> 00:27:59,067
I've lived a long life.

527
00:28:01,967 --> 00:28:04,333
I've been suffering
for a long time.

528
00:28:04,333 --> 00:28:07,667
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

529
00:28:07,667 --> 00:28:09,633
[NOA EXHALES, INHALES]

530
00:28:10,333 --> 00:28:13,200
- There's nothing I can do?
- Be happy for me.

531
00:28:14,967 --> 00:28:19,800
My dream is to serve
my family in the Philippines.

532
00:28:20,867 --> 00:28:22,233
And because of you...

533
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:27,267
We can stop this
from happening to others.

534
00:28:30,367 --> 00:28:32,100
Goodbye, Noa.

535
00:28:34,100 --> 00:28:36,267
Thank you for my happy ending.

536
00:28:38,700 --> 00:28:41,367
Please hug Ros for me.

537
00:28:43,333 --> 00:28:46,767
And please check
her blood pressure

538
00:28:46,767 --> 00:28:47,900
from time to time.

539
00:28:55,033 --> 00:29:01,300
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

540
00:29:01,333 --> 00:29:02,300
[LINDA INHALES]

541
00:29:07,933 --> 00:29:09,333
[WIND BLOWING]

542
00:29:10,300 --> 00:29:13,067
[EXHALES, CRIES]

543
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:21,033
[SNIFFLING, WHIMPERS]

544
00:29:22,333 --> 00:29:28,267
[SNIFFLES, CRYING]

545
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:33,300
[SNIFFLES, WHIMPERS]

546
00:29:35,233 --> 00:29:38,867
[NOA CRYING]

547
00:29:38,867 --> 00:29:40,033
[KNOCKING ON WINDOW]

548
00:29:41,800 --> 00:29:44,967
[SNIFFLES, EXHALES]

549
00:29:44,967 --> 00:29:45,933
[DOOR OPENS]

550
00:29:47,233 --> 00:29:48,267
[DOOR SHUTS]

551
00:29:49,467 --> 00:29:50,900
Did you hear?

552
00:29:51,900 --> 00:29:52,900
[NOA EXHALES SHAKILY]

553
00:29:54,100 --> 00:29:56,467
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

554
00:29:56,467 --> 00:29:57,500
[NOA CRYING]

555
00:29:59,400 --> 00:30:02,000
- [PATS BACK]
- [NOA CRYING]

556
00:30:03,067 --> 00:30:05,500
[NOA WHIMPERING]

557
00:30:06,900 --> 00:30:08,100
[NOA SNIFFLES]

558
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:12,033
We're still going to sue
those a-holes, right?

559
00:30:13,500 --> 00:30:14,533
- Come here.
- [NOA CHUCKLES]

560
00:30:15,300 --> 00:30:18,100
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

561
00:30:18,100 --> 00:30:20,133
[NOA BREATHES DEEPLY]

562
00:30:46,300 --> 00:30:47,433
(In Spanish) What are you doing?

563
00:30:47,433 --> 00:30:50,333
(In Spanish) Oh my god!
G-Grandma!

564
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:53,967
(In Spanish) You couldn't wait
until I was done?!

565
00:30:53,967 --> 00:30:56,100
(In Spanish) Oh, please.

566
00:30:56,100 --> 00:30:58,400
You act like
I haven't seen those before!

567
00:30:58,400 --> 00:30:59,500
So many times!

568
00:30:59,500 --> 00:31:00,500
[GRANDMA CHUCKLING]

569
00:31:01,833 --> 00:31:04,300
(In Spanish) But, how are
you here?

570
00:31:04,300 --> 00:31:06,133
Is this because of my rituals?

571
00:31:06,133 --> 00:31:08,800
(In Spanish) Oh, you missed me
so much.

572
00:31:09,300 --> 00:31:11,100
Uh, honestly...

573
00:31:11,567 --> 00:31:14,967
I regret not remembering
everything you taught me.

574
00:31:14,967 --> 00:31:16,000
(In Spanish) Well...

575
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:19,167
Sometimes it's better
to let things stay dead.

576
00:31:19,167 --> 00:31:22,000
If you really want this,
it means you miss me so much,

577
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:24,933
you wanna see dead people.

578
00:31:25,933 --> 00:31:27,900
(In Spanish) Oh, grandma...

579
00:31:27,900 --> 00:31:32,867
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

580
00:31:32,867 --> 00:31:35,200
Granny... Why now?

581
00:31:37,033 --> 00:31:38,567
(In Spanish) If I've
learned anything...

582
00:31:39,633 --> 00:31:45,167
It's the more the merrier.

583
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:47,467
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

584
00:31:48,333 --> 00:31:49,500
(In Spanish) Thank you, grandma.

585
00:31:55,667 --> 00:31:56,867
[GROANS]

586
00:31:58,567 --> 00:31:59,533
[LIQUID PLOPS]

587
00:32:02,033 --> 00:32:08,633
[LIQUID PLOPPING]

588
00:32:08,633 --> 00:32:13,533
[SCREAMING]

589
00:32:13,533 --> 00:32:20,133
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

